'''Carrot and stick''' is a term used to refer to the act of simultaneously rewarding good behaviour while punishing bad behaviour.

An alternative meaning comes from the visual image of the donkey, forever walking towards the carrot suspended from a stick, just out of reach of his mouth. In this context, the stick is not used as a punishment, but as a device to postpone fulfilment and encourage a reaction - in this case, forward movement. In copywriting, for example, a carrot on the stick would be the 'teaser' explaining just enough of a topic to interest the reader and bring a response to the offer in the promotion.


